fields.description:
As a seller, I would like to show my ads nicer on Facebook, so that people will click on it. See image of how it's showing right now. 

Current og:image tag that should be able to use a higher resolution one
{code:java}
<meta property="og:image" content="https://i.ebayimg.com/00/s/ODAwWDYwMA==/z/cIUAAOSw-QNa0~fS/$_19.JPG">
{code}

Facebook says: Use images that are at least 1200 x 630 pixels for the best display on high resolution devices. At the minimum, you should use images that are 600 x 315 pixels to display link page posts with larger images. If your image is smaller than 600 x 315 px, it will still display in the link page post, but the size will be much smaller.
https://louisem.com/3838/facebook-link-thumbnail-image-sizes. This site explains it well.

Current og:title tag that I would like to truncate the last part.
{code:java}
<meta property="og:title" content="Departamento Azcapotzalco Aquiles Serdán 2 Recamaras y 2 Cajones (A solo 15 minutos de Polanco) | San Mateo | Vivanuncios | 156787074">
{code}


----------
reference: https://wiki.vip.corp.ebay.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=EPS&title=EPS+Image+Sizes#EPSImageSizes-ListofalltheimagessupportedbyEPS

